rComments: Such a sweet lady, she's very knowledgeable on English literature & Canadian literature specifically! Gives great feedback on papers and has easy in class quizes for part of your grade. Go to class and you'll be fine! Would take a course just because she was teaching it in the future.

She has a quirky sense of humour and is sarcastic at times, but I would say she is nice. However, she marks very hard and she also said that "if we get a 70, 75, then we are doing well, and that she rarely ever gives As" I know that the standard is a lot higher in an academic university but her comments on my assignments were kind of mean in tone

She gives marks for attendance, 4 quizzes (easy), 4 assignments, and a final exam. According to her own words "I do not give out A's". Very discouraging prof! She is also very bias when marking papers. She wants to read her ideas with her word choices (which is impossible to do without her brain). Overall if you can choose anyone else, you should!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Had Keeler for a mandatory 1st year English poetry class and it was amazing! She posts her slides online but you still have to go to class for her analysis and explanation of the readings. She was fair with marking and gave clear expectations. Her lectures were so interesting and helpful, her class is super fun take it if you can!
